{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "Limits in Calculus" }}{PARA 
258 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 13 "(number6.mws)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
286 "The basic concept that defines \"Calculus\" it that of the \"limi
t.\"  The MAPLE command for computing the limit of some expression as \+
some variable goes to some value is     limit(expression, variable=val
ue);   Define the function f1 and perform the indicated sequence of MA
PLE commands.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "f1:=(x^3-x^2-8*x+12)/(x^2+x-6);" "6#>%#f1G*&,**$
%\"xG\"\"$\"\"\"*$F(\"\"#!\"\"*&\"\")F*F(F*F-\"#7F*F*,(*$F(F,F*F(F*\"
\"'F-F-" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "subs(x=4,f1);" }
}{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "limit(f1,x=4);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 
"> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 13 "subs(x=2,f1);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f1,x=2);" "6#-%&limitG6$%#f1G/%\"xG\"\"#" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "subs(x=-3,f1);" }}}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f1,x=-3);" "6#-%&limitG6$%#f1G/
%\"xG,$\"\"$!\"\"" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 109 "To see just what is going on here, factor the numerator \+
and denominator of f1 and notice the common factors. " }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 36 "factor(numer(f1));factor(denom(f1));" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 18 "Define g as below." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> \+
" 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 14 "g:=factor(f1);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
96 "Does the function g equal the function f?  To see that the answer \+
is \"no\" perform the following:" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 
1 0 79 "Limit(g,x=2)=limit(g,x=2);subs(x=2,g);Limit(g,x=-3)=limit(g,x=
-3);subs(x=-3,g);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 72 "Note that g is defi
ned and \"continuous\" at x=2 amd x=-3 while f1 is not." }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 105 "Now check the limiting behavior of f1 and 1/f1 at i
nfinity via the following sequence of MAPLE commands. " }}{PARA 0 "" 
0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "Limit(f
1,x=infinity)=limit(f1,x=infinity);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 44 "Limit(f1,x=-infinity)=limit(f1,x=-infinity);" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 46 "Limit(1/f1,x=infinity)=limit
(1/f1,x=infinity);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 32 "Limit
(1/f1,x=2)=limit(1/f1,x=2);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
44 "Limit(1/f1,x=2,right)=limit(1/f1,x=2,right);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 ">
 " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 42 "Limit(1/f1,x=2,left)=limit(1/f1,x=2,left);" }
}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 93 "Compute the partial fraction decomposit
ion of f1 and 1/f1 and see if these limits make sense." }}{EXCHG 
{PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 46 "convert(f1,parfrac,x);convert(1/f1,
parfrac,x);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 30 "Now plot the graphs of f1
 and " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "1/f1" "6#*&\"\"\"F$%#f1G!\"\"" }{TEXT -1 47 " t
o see if these limits make sense graphically." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 17 "plot(f1,x=-3
..3);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 31 "plot(1/f1,x=-10..1
0,y=-10..10);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 342 "1.  For each of the following functions compute the indi
cated substitutions and limits, and plot the graph to see if the limit
ing behavior looks correct.  Recall that a function is called \"contin
uous a x=a\" if its value at x=a equals its limit at x=a.  In each cas
e say whether the function is, or is not, continuous at the point in q
uestion." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "f2:=(-2*x-4)/(x^3+
2*x^2);" "6#>%#f2G*&,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"%\"xGF)!\"\"\"\"%F+F),&*$F*\"\"$F)*
&F(F)*$F*F(F)F)F+" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "subs(x=0,f2);" "6#-%%subsG6$/%
\"xG\"\"!%#f2G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f2,x=0);" "6#-%&limitG6$
%#f2G/%\"xG\"\"!" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "subs(x=2,f2);" "6#-%%subsG6$/%
\"xG\"\"#%#f2G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f2,x=2);" "6#-%&limitG6$
%#f2G/%\"xG\"\"#" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "f3:=(1+h)^(1/h);" "6#>%#f3G),&
\"\"\"F'%\"hGF'*&F'F'F(!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "subs(h=0,f3);" "6#-%
%subsG6$/%\"hG\"\"!%#f3G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "
" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f3,h=0);" "6#-%&lim
itG6$%#f3G/%\"hG\"\"!" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }
}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "f4:=sin(x)/x;" "6#>%#f4G*&-%
$sinG6#%\"xG\"\"\"F)!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 
"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "subs(x=0,f4);" "6#-%%sub
sG6$/%\"xG\"\"!%#f4G" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f4,x=0);" "6#-%&limitG6
$%#f4G/%\"xG\"\"!" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 40 "2.  Similarly consider the behavior of  \+
" }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "sin(1/x)" "6#-%$sinG6#*&\"\"\"F'%\"xG!\"\"" }{TEXT 
-1 4 "  , " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "x*sin(1/x)" "6#*&%\"xG\"\"\"-%$sinG6#*&F%F
%F$!\"\"F%" }{TEXT -1 8 "  , and " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "x^2*sin(1/x)" "6#*&
%\"xG\"\"#-%$sinG6#*&\"\"\"F*F$!\"\"F*" }{TEXT -1 12 "  near x=0 ." }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "f5:=piecewise(x=0,0,sin(1/x));" "6#>%#f5G-%*piecewise
G6%/%\"xG\"\"!F*-%$sinG6#*&\"\"\"F/F)!\"\"" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(f5,x=0);" "6#-%&limitG6$%#f5G/%\"xG\"\"!" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 34 "     a.  Plot the graph of f5 and " }
{TEXT 256 28 "explain the MAPLE output for" }{TEXT -1 2 "  " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "limit(f5,x=0)" "6#-%&limitG6$%#f5G/%\"xG\"\"!" }{TEXT 
-1 4 "  . " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "
