0 "" {TEXT -1 33 "Compute the following limits and " }{TEXT 260 129 "c
omment on what the results tell us about the relative growth rates of \+
the two functions involved with the quotient in each case." }}{PARA 0 
"" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(
x/ln(x),x=0);" "6#-%&limitG6$*&%\"xG\"\"\"-%#lnG6#F'!\"\"/F'\"\"!" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 261 9 "Comments." }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(x/ln(x),x=infinity);" "6#-%&limitG6$*
&%\"xG\"\"\"-%#lnG6#F'!\"\"/F'%)infinityG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 0 "" }{TEXT 262 9 "Comments." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 
19 1 "limit(x^100/exp(x),x=infinity);" "6#-%&limitG6$*&%\"xG\"$+\"-%$e
xpG6#F'!\"\"/F'%)infinityG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 
263 9 "Comments." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(ln(x
)/sqrt(x),x=infinity);" "6#-%&limitG6$*&-%#lnG6#%\"xG\"\"\"-%%sqrtG6#F
*!\"\"/F*%)infinityG" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 264 9 "C
omments." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
113 "Let's consider a multivariable limit.  Investigate the limiting b
ehavior with the limit and plot commands for the" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 9 "function " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(x^2-y^2)/(x^2+y^2)" "6#*&,&*$%
\"xG\"\"#\"\"\"*$%\"yGF'!\"\"F(,&*$F&F'F(*$F*F'F(F+" }{TEXT -1 70 " . \+
 For example the MAPLE command for computing this limit at (1,2) is" }
}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 76 "Limit((x^2-y^2)/(x^2+y^2),[x,y]=[1,0])=limit((x^2-y^2)/(x^2+y^2)
,\{x=1,y=0\});" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 51 "Now compute the limit \+
at (1,0), (0,1), and (0,0).  " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 
0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 48 "Plot the graph and see if the l
imits make sense." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 150 "Recall t
he definition of the \"difference quotient for a function G\".  Namely
, if G (x) is a function then the difference quotient is defined as   \+
    " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {XPPEDIT 18 0 "(G(x+h)-G(x))/h " "6#*&,&-%\"GG
6#,&%\"xG\"\"\"%\"hGF*F*-F&6#F)!\"\"F*F+F." }{TEXT -1 23 "  , or equiv
alently    " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(G(x)-G(h))/(x-h)" "6#*&,&-%\"GG6#%\"xG\"
\"\"-F&6#%\"hG!\"\"F),&F(F)F,F-F-" }{TEXT -1 9 "     .   " }}{PARA 0 "
" 0 "" {TEXT 265 51 "What does the difference quotient actually measur
e?" }{TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 139 "For each of the fo
llowing functions compute its difference quotient and then compute the
 limit of the difference quotient as h goes to 0.  " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "
" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "g1:=x->(2*x+
3)^5;" "6#>%#g1GR6#%\"xG7\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowG6\"*$,&*&\"\"#\"\"\"F'
F1F1\"\"$F1\"\"&F,F,F," }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "dqg
1:=(g1(x+h)-g1(x))/h;" "6#>%%dqg1G*&,&-%#g1G6#,&%\"xG\"\"\"%\"hGF,F,-F
(6#F+!\"\"F,F-F0" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "limit(dqg
1,h=0);" "6#-%&limitG6$%%dqg1G/%\"hG\"\"!" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "
" {MPLTEXT 1 0 10 "factor(%);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 44 "Continue in the same way for g2, g3, and \+
g4." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{XPPEDIT 19 1 "g2:=x->ln(x);" "6#>%#g2GR6#%\"xG7\"6$%)operatorG%&arrow
G6\"-%#lnG6#F'F,F,F," }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}
}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 1 "g3:=x->1/x;" "6#>%#g3GR6#%\"x
G7\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowG6\"*&\"\"\"F.F'!\"\"F,F,F," }}}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {XPPEDIT 19 
1 "g4:=x->sin(a*x);" "6#>%#g4GR6#%\"xG7\"6$%)operatorG%&arrowG6\"-%$si
nG6#*&%\"aG\"\"\"F'F2F,F,F," }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 
